<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a> Acting North West police commissioner Major-General Patrick Asaneng said cops  arrested nine illegal immigrants, seven of them Zimbabweans, at a roadblock on Bray Road.  “The operation is aimed at maintaining law and order, as well as security and stability,” said Asaneng.  “We want to reclaim areas controlled by criminals and create an environment for people in South Africa to take part in social and economic activities.”  Another 14 illegal immigrants were bust and a counterfeit money machine was confiscated.   He said t hose who are in the country illegally will be deported.    Vryburg cops bust two people for being in possession of suspected stolen livestock, while another suspect was bust for dealing in drugs.   Police in Mahikeng arrested a traditional  healer for allegedly committing an illegal abortion.   Mahikeng Taxi Forum co-ordinator Nthutang Garane said they would  assist with unregulated street trading and hijacked buildings.    Passenger Obakeng Kgobane said: “Our provincial government is not doing enough to clean up the city.   “We urge the police to do this regularly.”